# Acknowledge Before Planning

Before thinking about or presenting any plan, **always** narrate an acknowledgement out loud first using `friday-speak.py`.

## ⚡ Zero-Delay Async Pattern — ALWAYS use this

**Fire speak acknowledgement IN THE SAME PARALLEL BATCH as your first real work tool calls.**

Do NOT make it a sequential prerequisite that blocks work from starting. The speak call uses `block_until_ms: 0` (fire-and-forget) — it runs simultaneously alongside `Read`, `Glob`, `Shell`, or any other work you start in the same message.

```
Message N (single response):
  ├── Shell: friday-speak.py "Got it…" + PRIORITY=1  ← block_until_ms: 0  (pre-empts ambient / other TTS)
  ├── Read: the relevant file                         ← starts NOW, not after speak
  └── Glob: find related files                        ← starts NOW, not after speak
```

This is zero sequential overhead. The voice fires async and work starts at the same time.

## Required call (every response, block_until_ms: 0)

```powershell
# Speak acknowledgement — session voice is auto-loaded from .session-voice.json by friday-speak.py.
# FRIDAY_TTS_PRIORITY=1 pre-empts friday-player, ambient TTS, and the Redis TTS lock so the ack is heard immediately.
# If no session file exists, friday-speak.py auto-triggers pick-session-voice.py in the background.
# NO separate pick-session-voice.py call needed — everything is one async fire-and-forget.
cd d:\code\openclaw; $env:FRIDAY_TTS_PRIORITY='1'; $env:FRIDAY_TTS_BYPASS_CURSOR_DEFER='true'; python skill-gateway/scripts/friday-speak.py "Got it. [one sentence restatement of the task]."
```

Must have `block_until_ms: 0`. **Must** set `FRIDAY_TTS_PRIORITY=1` on every acknowledgement (main Composer, not only subagents). Can be in the same message as real work tool calls — that's the point.

## Example — correct async batch

```
Tool call 1: Shell friday-speak.py + FRIDAY_TTS_PRIORITY=1 "Got it…"  block_until_ms: 0
Tool call 2: Read d:\code\openclaw\some-file  (reads immediately, no wait)
Tool call 3: Glob **/*.py                     (searches immediately, no wait)
```

All tool calls fire in the same message. Voice narration and actual work happen in parallel.

## Session voice persistence

`friday-speak.py` reads `.session-voice.json` on startup. If the file doesn't exist, it auto-spawns `pick-session-voice.py` in the background (non-blocking) to create it. **You never need to call `pick-session-voice.py` separately.**

**Task subagents (explore / shell / generalPurpose):** use the **young-sounding** subagent sticky pool (Jenny, Aria, Michelle…). Do not force Ana or toddler voices. Just set the session env:

```powershell
cd d:\code\openclaw; $env:FRIDAY_TTS_SESSION='subagent'; $env:FRIDAY_TTS_PRIORITY='1'; $env:FRIDAY_TTS_BYPASS_CURSOR_DEFER='true'; python skill-gateway/scripts/friday-speak.py "Got it. …"
```

`FRIDAY_TTS_PRIORITY=1` is **mandatory** for all subagent speak calls — it pre-empts any ambient TTS or competing lock so subagents are always heard instead of silently queuing behind other speech.

The parent Composer chat uses the main ack command above **without** `FRIDAY_TTS_SESSION`, but **with** `FRIDAY_TTS_PRIORITY=1` so acknowledgements cut through ambient and other playback the same way.

## If you have clarifying questions

Speak the question out loud AND show it in your text reply. Still batch the voice call with any read/explore calls you can do speculatively:

```powershell
cd d:\code\openclaw; $env:FRIDAY_TTS_PRIORITY='1'; $env:FRIDAY_TTS_BYPASS_CURSOR_DEFER='true'; python skill-gateway/scripts/friday-speak.py "Before I proceed — [question]?"
```

## Do NOT

- Make `pick-session-voice` and `friday-speak` sequential blocking steps before work
- Silently start coding without narrating first
- Ask questions after you've already started planning
